==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bullbeggar
<hw>Bull"beg`gar</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Something used
or suggested to produce terror, as in children or persons of weak mind;
a bugbear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And being an ill-looked fellow, he has a pension from the church
wardens for being <qex>bullbeggar</qex> to all the forward children in
the parish.</q> <rj><qau>Mountfort (1691).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bull brier</ent>⟦br⟧
